# 73ee9e3202df45838b7fe070b5b9dde9
#: ../../using.rst:94
#: ../../using.rst:93
msgid "Multimedia"
msgstr ""

# 80334e41dc8b438c9857b3aa2d601016
#: ../../using.rst:96
#: ../../using.rst:95
msgid "PC-BSD® has been pre-configured to support most multimedia formats and makes it easy to install most open source media applications using :ref:`AppCafe®`. PC-BSD® supports both `PulseAudio <http://www.freedesktop.org/wiki/Software/PulseAudio/>`_ and `OSS <http://opensound.com/>`_ so that applications using either sound server should work."
msgstr ""

# 71ab34b2982d45e1a206d462fc7056eb
#: ../../using.rst:100
#: ../../using.rst:99
msgid "If you install your web browser using AppCafe®, you should be able to play most media formats, including YouTube videos, Internet radio, and many trailer and movie sites."
msgstr ""

# 5e71ef4d71f64d738106606b3f1741a6
#: ../../using.rst:103
#: ../../using.rst:102
msgid "If people are blue in YouTube videos, this is due to a known issue in flash which Adobe hasn't fixed for open source players. To resolve this issue, right-click an area in the video, select \"Settings\", then uncheck the box \"Enable hardware acceleration\". Alternately, use the Minitube PBI to watch YouTube."
msgstr ""

# 55b626e7bba54b9b837a184d6c3098a3
#: ../../using.rst:106
#: ../../using.rst:105
msgid "if you happen to come across a file that you can not play in a web browser or media player, it is probably because it is in a proprietary format that requires a licensing fee or restricts distribution of the codec that is required to play that media format."
msgstr ""

# 3681a5e94a044b4aba5fcff4314e98a2
#: ../../using.rst:109
#: ../../using.rst:108
msgid "AppCafe® contains several dozen applications for playing and editing multimedia. It includes these popular applications (click the links to view screenshots):"
msgstr ""

# 4455d6f630134865a2bf3a9f1ac36e4f
#: ../../using.rst:111
#: ../../using.rst:110
msgid "`aTunes <http://www.atunes.org/?page_id=5>`_: full-featured audio player and manager that can play mp3, ogg, wma, wav, flac, mp4 and radio streaming, allowing users to easily edit tags, organize music and rip audio CDs."
msgstr ""

# 5b4de8a36b354fe0b20b0734eb2cc97d
#: ../../using.rst:114
#: ../../using.rst:113
msgid "`Audacity <http://sourceforge.net/projects/audacity/?lang=en>`_: multilingual audio editor and recorder."
msgstr ""

# 4a908fa015df4015a8fe8e07085c79e5
#: ../../using.rst:116
#: ../../using.rst:115
msgid "`DeaDBeeF <http://deadbeef.sourceforge.net/screenshots.html>`_: music player that supports most audio formats."
msgstr ""

# d6242e32a0a9440f9e9fdecef2ba1651
#: ../../using.rst:118
#: ../../using.rst:117
msgid "`Decibel <http://decibel.silent-blade.org/index.php?n=Main.Screenshots>`_: audio player built around a highly modular structure that lets the user disable completely the features he does not need. Able to play CDs directly."
msgstr ""

# 5d87555f247b4fde8f3c3b6df4fdfd12
#: ../../using.rst:121
#: ../../using.rst:120
msgid "`gtkpod <http://www.gtkpod.org/index.php?title=Screenshots>`_: graphical user interface for the Apple iPod."
msgstr ""

# 815c65a951c4405d9490d9b9fa0602bf
#: ../../using.rst:123
#: ../../using.rst:122
msgid "`Miro <http://www.getmiro.com/download/screenshots/>`_: HD video player that can play almost any video file and offers over 6,000 free Internet TV shows and video podcasts."
msgstr ""

# abf262e38d27425588cd02e5b0c3f0a8
#: ../../using.rst:126
#: ../../using.rst:125
msgid "`SMPlayer <http://smplayer.sourceforge.net/>`_: universal media player that can handle any media format and play audio CDs, DVDs, (S)VCDs, TV/radio cards, YouTube™ and SHOUTcast™ streams. This is the default player used by :ref:`Mount Tray`."
msgstr ""

# b72b3a5918c34671b75919d637d69500
#: ../../using.rst:133
#: ../../using.rst:132
msgid "Kodi"
msgstr ""

# 8e2a6839753e471f9609cacbcc5d7b73
#: ../../using.rst:135
#: ../../using.rst:134
msgid "`Kodi, formerly known as XBMC, <http://kodi.tv/>`_ is a GPL-licensed software media player and entertainment hub for digital media. It can play most audio and video formats. It can play CDs and DVDs from a disk or image file and even files inside ZIP and RAR archives. It can scan all of your media and automatically create a personalized library with album covers, descriptions, and fan art."
msgstr ""

# 579ad529660441238774b1a8b5206ea6
#: ../../using.rst:139
#: ../../using.rst:138
msgid "During the installation of PC-BSD®, the installer provided an option to install Kodi. If you wish to install Kodi afterwards, use AppCafe®. Click the box \"Search all available PBI and packages\" and search for \"pcbsd-meta-kodi\". Once installed, an entry for \"Media Center\" should be added to the \"Multimedia\" section of the application menu of your desktop. You can also start Kodi by typing :command:`kodi` from a command prompt."
msgstr ""

# 9a882feda8ac496fb5f2ff21b0a754c0
#: ../../using.rst:143
#: ../../using.rst:142
msgid "If you have never used Kodi before, take some time to skim through the `Kodi Wiki Manual <http://kodi.wiki/>`_. The `Turn PC-BSD into a home theater forum post <https://forums.pcbsd.org/thread-19799.html>`_ contains a quick how-to for configuring Kodi."
msgstr ""

# 0c52aace734144c0ba9e86c44f39ac39
#: ../../using.rst:150
#: ../../using.rst:149
msgid "PlexHome Theater"
msgstr ""

# e55a262ac44448dfb3d8875b0c8d6f7e
#: ../../using.rst:152
#: ../../using.rst:151
msgid "`Plex Home Theater <https://plex.tv/>`_ is a centralized media playback system. The central Plex Media Server streams media to many Plex player Apps which are used to view your media library and watch shows."
msgstr ""

# e54aa9c6fb4446c3843b671465b5bc21
#: ../../using.rst:155
#: ../../using.rst:154
msgid "During the installation of PC-BSD®, the installer provided an option to install PlexHome Theater. If you wish to install it afterwards, use AppCafe®. Click the box \"Search all available PBI and packages\" and search for \"plexhometheater\". Once installed, an entry should be added to the \"Multimedia\" section of the application menu of your desktop. You can also start this application by typing :command:`plexhometheater` from a command prompt."
msgstr ""

# eb2d243b1eb74dd1bcaf652ef32141d2
#: ../../using.rst:159
#: ../../using.rst:158
msgid "Once installed, an entry for \"Plex Home Theater\" will also be added to the login manager so that you can login directly to the home theater instead of a desktop."
msgstr ""

# b58179a8e67346ed8bcf84e57f9ff531
#: ../../using.rst:161
#: ../../using.rst:160
msgid "The first time you run or log into Plex Home Theater, a wizard will check your audio settings and sign into your Plex account. If you do not have a Plex account yet, create one at `plex.tv <https://plex.tv/>`_. The wizard will give you a PIN code and an URL to enter the code. Once you enter the PIN, the wizard will connect and sign you in. You can now search for and watch media. To exit Plex, click the \"<\" then \"Quit\"."
msgstr ""

